st - simple terminal
--------------------
st is a simple terminal emulator for X which sucks less.


Patches/Changes
---------------
- Scrollback patch
  - Scroll up/down with 'pkup/pgdown'
  - Or mousewheel up/down
- Copy/Paste with 'alt + c/v'
- Zoom in/out with 'alt + +/-' 
  - Reset with 'alt + ='
- Font2 patch
  - Tamzen as default font
  - Symbola as backup
- Externalpipe patch
  - Uses 2 simple scripts to follow/copy urls on screen using dmenu
  - follow url with $BROWSER with 'alt + o'
    - $BROWSER is set to surf in script.
  - copy url with 'alt+y'
- Personal colortheme


Requirements
------------
In order to build st you need the Xlib header files.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (st is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install st (if
necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running st
----------
If you did not install st with make clean install, you must compile
the st terminfo entry with the following command:

    tic -sx st.info

See the man page for additional details.

